  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Organisational strengthening for growth and effectiveness</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">African Initiatives is a social justice organisation working in Ghana and Tanzania. It also undertakes global education in the UK. It works with partners to empower communities to claim their rights. African Initiatives provides partners with capacity building in key areas. In 2011, with assistance from Comic Relief, INTRAC, KPMG and DFID, the organisation carried out a series of self-assessments which produced recommendations for governance, strategy, finance, fundraising, monitoring and advocacy work. African Initiatives wishes to determine its future direction; strategic objectives and indicators need to be set and monitored over the next five years. Governance systems require strengthening as the organisation grows, seeks out new partnerships and invests in key positions for fundraising and marketing. As income from institutional grants grows it will be important to modify and align African Initiative&apos;s financial management systems too.</narrative>
  </description>
